The Herald JOHANNESBURG. – Many celebrities with established careers have gone back to school and pursued higher education. With almost 26 years of the music business, Kalawa Jazmee boss Oscar “Oskido” Mdlongwa has decided to further his studies at the University of Pretoria by doing a five-month course in Project Management. “Today I embark on a new challenge by going back to school. I have enrolled at the University of Pretoria for a 5-month Project Management Programme. That’s 8 am to 5 pm, 1 week per month. Believers let’s keep growing and empowering ourselves,” he shared the exciting news with his followers on social media. Oskido decided to go back to school because he wanted to challenge himself. – News24.com